The federal judge ruled a jury should decide whether the police departments for Lakewood and Fife acted within their policies when a SWAT team shot and killed a drunken and despondent man as he held his 4-year-old son during a standoff.

A federal judge has refused to dismiss a civil-rights lawsuit against two Pierce County police departments and a multidepartment SWAT team after finding evidence that police violated the Constitution and their own internal policies when they used armored vehicles
